<br>
Here's my thinking on rejuv vs enhance. First off I almost always forget to turn on speed of angel our 17% haste spell. When I do remember I usually cancel it very shortly so I don't use up too much power. So basically I'm hardly using my 5spec pts in enhance at all. Now with 5pts in rejuv I'm using my heals all the time soloing and grouping. With consistent 40pt+ heals I just need a few casts after soloing a yellow and I'm back in business. Even though I can't heal as well as a cleric I feel much safer knowing that most my heals now are 40+ instead of the wild swings I was getting with just 3pts in rejuv. Nothing worse than healing that tank for 12pts and watching him die <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
I've read where people are saying go mostly staff and enhance and let the cleric do the healing but I'm not seeing a whole hell of a lot of clerics out there. Seems that 90% of the classes are melee oriented. Even if you do have a cleric I feel better knowing that my healing variance is much tighter now to help back him up.<br>
<br>
Well anyway, time for some sleep. I'll say this, that staff of life just plain rocks. Never dreamed soloing yellows would be this easy. Need to try it on some oranges soon. <p>[55 Defiler]<b> Dravula Nerferatu</b> (Dark Elf) <br>
